            <title>[TIKA-319] HtmlParser - use encoding hint only if charset is supported</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-319</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Encoding hint should be considered only if that encoding is supported.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Diff of my fix:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8212; HtmlParser.java	(wersja 835302)&lt;br/&gt;
+++ HtmlParser.java	(kopia robocza)&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -46,7 +46,7 @@&lt;br/&gt;
         // Prepare the input source using the encoding hint if available&lt;br/&gt;
         InputSource source = new InputSource(stream); &lt;br/&gt;
         String encoding = metadata.get(Metadata.CONTENT_ENCODING); &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if (encoding != null) {&lt;br/&gt;
+        if (encoding != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; Charset.isSupported(encoding)) 
{ 
             source.setEncoding(encoding);
         }&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
